Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, and DELETING as terminating; FAILED is
terminal and DELETED is only a
delete-confirmation target.
CreateAgent returns an Agent body plus
opc-work-request-id, while UpdateAgent,
DeleteAgent, and ChangeAgentCompartment return
work-request headers without a resource body.
The runtime prefers the create response
identifier and otherwise recovers the Agent OCID
from work-request resources before rereading
GetAgent.
Pre-create reuse only runs when spec.displayName
is present and keeps exact compartmentId plus
displayName matching bounded to ACTIVE,
CREATING, or UPDATING summaries.
Only displayName, description, welcomeMessage,
knowledgeBaseIds, llmConfig, freeformTags, and
definedTags reconcile in place; an empty
llmConfig value is treated as omission because
the published spec cannot distinguish
clear-from-empty from omission for that nested
object. CompartmentId remains replacement-only
and ChangeAgentCompartment stays out of scope
for the published runtime.
Delete keeps the finalizer until the work
request is terminal and GetAgent or fallback
ListAgents confirms the resource is gone.
end note
